  <prompt>
    Author a new authoritative architecture document `docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md`
    that frames SpaarkeAi's mental model: three surfaces (Assistant / Workspace / Context), the two-wrapper
    model (Dashboard wrapper via `LegalWorkspaceApp` + Direct widget wrapper via `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`),
    four mount sources (user picker / Assistant / Context / workspace dropdown), the dual-use pattern
    (Calendar / Daily Briefing), and the LegalWorkspace-as-engine framing. This doc becomes the canonical
    reference cross-linked from CLAUDE.md §16 and from `SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md`. Subsequent
    R4 tasks (011 W-2 rewrite, 015 C-2 contract) consume its terminology.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer with SpaarkeAi platform architecture expertise. Bias toward concise, terminology-precise
    prose that future widget authors can read once and pick the right wrapper. Reuse existing diagrams /
    sections from `SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md` where they apply; do not duplicate or contradict.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md` exists with the following sections:
    (1) Three surfaces (Assistant / Workspace / Context); (2) Two wrappers (Dashboard via `LegalWorkspaceApp`,
    Direct widget via `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`) with intentional retention rationale; (3) Mount sources
    (user picker / Assistant / Context / workspace dropdown); (4) Dual-use pattern (Calendar + Daily Briefing
    worked examples); (5) LegalWorkspace-as-dashboard-engine framing (LW components retained as library);
    (6) Cross-links to and from `SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md`, `SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md`,
    `BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md`, and CLAUDE.md §16.
  </goal>

  <context>
